voice, to communicate the range of human emotions. Why would we deprive ourselves of that?', 11991, 0), (278987, 'A diplomat who says “yes” means “maybe", a diplomat who says “maybe" means “no”, and a diplomat who says “no” is no diplomat.', 10858, 0), (278988, 'Communication is an art and a meaningful conversation is a masterpiece.', 12168, 0), (278989, 'Clarity of thought is a must for brevity in speech.', 21649, 0), (278990, 'Staring into someone’s eyes for a long time is psychic. At first it’s very strange and scary - scarier than the first time you have sex. Then you begin to relax, and the person you’re looking at may become very beautiful. As you look into their eyes, you may see them change sex or race. You can see the child in an old person and a young person may appear ancient. Just looking into someone’s eyes for a long time can be trippier than taking acid.', 39034, 0), (278991, 'Coming from a business family, she shied away from abstractions.', 19676, 0), (278992, 'He did what good lawyers always do. He shifted his argument in the direction his audience was already going.', 19681, 0), (278993, 'A dash of humor will only add intense gravity to the proceedings, even as a flash of lightning only makes midnight dreariness all the more impressive.', 771, 0), (278994, 'All conversation, big or small, is about painting word pictures of your experiences for other people. The more', 19680, 0), (278995, 'Pausing gives us the opportunity to arrive at an internal place from which we can choose wisely what needs to be done or said, and then do so gently.', 47532, 0), (278996, 'One thought fixed upon the mind will be better than 50 thoughts flittering across the ear.', 771, 0), (278997, 'In this slipshod age, we need object lessons in language and thought. – Edith Wharton on an address by John Hay', 19687, 0), (278998, 'Most of us make assumptions about how someone will relate to us, and they are often unfounded.', 10422, 0), (278999, 'Frankie, I''m fully awake and more curious than George. If we hang up I''ll lie here formulating a million reasons for your call, none of them your truth, and that would drive me crazy. You wouldn''t do that to the guy who has your grandmother''s old phone number, would you? Trust me, you can tell me anything.—Emerson', 7680, 0), (279000, 'When communication in unclear speculations takes precedence.', 46814, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (279001, 'I found myself speaking more slowly (in an attempt to obey the Bible in speech), as if I was speaking French instead of English.', 2233, 0), (279002, 'You don''t talk dirty to make him hot. You "talk dirty" to communicate what you need. And most guys, if you go, "Yeah, yeah, just like that, a little more to the left," they''ll do it.', 42435, 0), (279003, 'Communication land lines are going to be around for a long time, the internet runs on them, as do the wireless cell phone towers.', 5008, 0), (279004, 'Real communication is not possible. That is why my message, your perception and your expression shall never be the same.', 1657, 0), (279005, 'Suddenly I''ve become so restless that I''m capable of saying "That is enough" and ending what I''m writing you, which is based mostly on blind words.', 3416, 0), (279006, 'G-rated language is making me a less angry person. Behavior shapes emotion.', 2233, 0), (279007, 'What does it mean to be an advocate? INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (279051, 'Quality speaks by itself. Rightly communicated it creates Joy. Like an Infant needs no words to express to her mother. Any success of communication enhances beauty of both, which too needs no words to endorse.', 19470, 0), (279052, 'The only difference between people who say they cannot perceive interdimensionally and people who consciously communicate interdimensionally is intent and practice. Most people access interdimensional information unconsciously. When they experience conscious contact with a non-human energy, they tend to pass it off as a curiosity or as intuition, or they cancel out the experience as too weird to deal with.', 47539, 0), (279053, 'The concert we give is winning. And if all the people in our organization whose instrument is scouting of player development or major league scouting or player knowledge, all play well, we''re going to have the most beautiful symphony of success. And I think we have.', 47540, 0), (279054, 'I''m watching you, big boy, my eyes say, but his are closed so it''s an optical monologue.', 26780, 0), (279055, 'If you have a room which you do not want certain people to get into, put a lock on it for which they do not have the key. But there is no point in talking to them about it, unless of course you want them to admire the room from outside! The honorable thing to do is put a lock on the door which will be noticed only by those who can open it, not by the rest.', 1163, 0), (279056, 'He knew very well that the great majority of human conversation is meaningless. A man can get through most of his days on stock answers to stock questions, he thought. Once he catches onto the game, he can manage with an assortment of grunts. This would not be so if people listened to each other, but they don''t. They know that no one is going to say anything moving and important to them at that very moment. Anything important will be announced in the newspapers and reprinted for those who missed it. No one really wants to know how his neighbor is feeling, but he asks him anyway, because it is polite, and because he knows that his neighbor certainly will not tell him how he feels. What this woman and I say to each other is not important. It is the simple making of sounds that pleases us.', 610, 0), (279057, 'Most of the time, communication gets confused with conversation. In fact, the two are distinctly different.', 1798, 0), (279058, 'He was a man with a chest, and he wanted to give thoughtful expression to the passion of his heart.', 47541, 0), (279059, '�Communication and a clear mutual understanding between two or more people builds the best route to success in any venture. I don’t expect…* immediate action, * instant perfection, * total comprehension* complete implementation, or * flawless execution. I do expect the best communication and honest effort to create the best plans for the best results while being able to stay on the same page as much as possible. If that concept doesn’t work for you, then you won’t be working with me.', 8380, 0), (279060, 'One journalist complemented another that his article on a dispute, "had made both sides see themselves as they are.', 17905, 0), (279061, 'Great Leaders develop through a never ending process of self-study, self-reflection, education, training, and experience', 44065, 0), (279062, 'Oh.” It was one those ohs that came packed with layers of meaning — none of which merely meant oh.', 6743, 0), (279063, 'There''s the emotional work that comes with living with someone who''s not you and who therefore has different preferences ans styles of communicating. She might prefer to talk for three days straight if that''s what it takes to resolve an argument, while you would rather fill your pockets with granite and walk into the ocean.', 47542, 0), (279064, 'Make it so obvious even a computer couldn''t be confused.', 42457, 0), (279065, 'When you listen to someone, you should give up all your preconceived ideas and your subjective opinions; you should just listen to him, just observe what his way is. We put very little emphasis on right and wrong or good and bad. We just see things as they are with him, and accept them. This is how we communicate with each other. Usually when you listen to some statement, you hear it as a kind of echo of yourself. You are actually listening to your own opinion. If it agrees with your opinion you may accept it, but if it does not, you will reject it or you may not even really hear it.', 2504, 0), (279066, 'True communication depends upon our being straightforward with one another... But the best way to communicate may be just to sit without saying anything.', 2504, 0), (279067, 'Gestures are all that I have; sometimes they must be grand in nature. And while I occasionally step over the line and into the world of the melodramatic, it is what I must do in order to communicate clearly and effectively. In order to make my point understood without question.', 1128, 0), (279068, 'I''m sorry to bother you," she whispered. "When I get excited about a movie I want to talk. I can''t help it.', 4084, 0), (279069, 'He is hard, frozen ice cream and I am a weak spoon. What I''ve learned is this: You don''t get much ice cream for all the hard work you put in, and the spoon ends up bent.', 18846, 0), (279070, 'A mind full of preconceived ideas, subjective intentions, or habits it not open to things as they are.', 2504, 0), (279071, 'An ancient sage held that in different ages, humans held the senses in different ratios, according to the media by which they communicated and expressed themselves. Hence before writing, the ear was the royal sense. After writing, the eye.', 47543, 0), (279072, 'Women tend to communicate early and often about a problem. Men are more likely to view communication as a tool, and when they see it as the wrong tool for the job, they believe it should be stored neatly in the toolbox.', 47544, 0), (279073, 'Understanding what is being said is only a fraction of the task of communicating. Taking in signals from the entire context is critical.', 11254, 0), (279074, 'Contradictions, in any communication, are the first stepping stones of mistrust', 42051, 0), (279075, 'We have to talk more. I need you to know what we need to talk about. In fact, don’t decide what is and isn’t important to share with me, it all is—from the mundane to the shocking. If something upsets you? Tell me. Make me a part of your life in such a deep way that I don’t feel separate from it. I don’t ever want to feel like you’re keeping things from me again, even if it’s unintentional.', 34746, 0), (279076, 'Because, of course, it wouldn''t do to just talk to her. She had spoken to him in flashes of daylight, and he felt he ought to reply in kind.', 4084, 0), (279077, 'The turning point for effective communication is actually hearing what is being said, rather than hearing what you want to hear instead.', 4705, 0), (279078, 'So without any intentional, fancy way of adjusting yourself, to express yourself freely as you are is the most important thing to make yourself happy, and to make others happy... So we should be concentrated with our full mind and body on what we do; and we should be faithful, subjectively and objectively, to ourselves, and especially to our feelings... it is better to express how you feel without any particular attachment or intention.', 2504, 0), (279079, 'After simmering years of censorship and repression, the masses finally throng the streets. The chants echoing off the walls to build to a roar from all directions, stoking the courage of the crowds as they march on the center of the capital. Activists inside each column maintain contact with each other via text messages; communications centers receive reports and broadcast them around the city; affinity groups plot the movements of the police via digital mapping. A rebel army of bloggers uploads video footage for all the world to see as the two hosts close for battle. Suddenly, at the moment of truth, the lines go dead. The insurgents look up from the blank screens of their cell phones to see the sun reflecting off the shields of the advancing riot police, who are still guided by close circuits of fully networked technology. The rebels will have to navigate by dead reckoning against a hyper-informed adversary. All this already happened, years ago, when President Mubarak shut down the communications grid during the Egyptian uprising of 2011. A generation hence, when the same scene recurs, we can imagine the middle-class protesters - the cybourgeoisie - will simply slump forward, blind and deaf and wracked by seizures as the microchips in their cerebra run haywire, and it will be up to the homeless and destitute to guide them to safety.', 4739, 0), (279080, 'You can''t solve problems until you understand the other side." –Jeffrey Manber', 32848, 0), (279081, 'When you draw a line in the sand, be careful it is not low tide.', 23474, 0), (279082, 'If you don''t know the question, you are not ready for the answer.', 3555, 0), (279083, 'The communication with God is very important, because the communication is one of our greatest needs, and God is the most important one we need.', 24825, 0), (279084, 'We can only guess at the thoughts and emotions of our neighbors. Each one of us is a prisoner in a solitary tower and he communicates with the other prisoners, who form mankind, by conventional signs that have not quite the same meaning for them as for himself.', 235, 0), (279085, 'Body language speaks much more succinctly and honestly than mere spoken words.', 23474, 0), (279086, 'There’s a much different message received, when the signs written in the flesh were not in your hand writing.', 23474, 0), (279087, 'When Internet parlance finds its way into our accepted vocabulary, it becomes a cliché.', 42051, 0), (279088, 'When it comes to texting the power of you thumbs compel you', 3034, 0), (279089, 'Perhaps we now need to engineer scarcity in our communications, in our interactions, and in the things we consume. Otherwise our lives become like a Morse code transmission that''s lacking breaks - a swarm of noise blanketing the valuable data beneath.', 11790, 0), (279090, 'a lack of communication is preferable to a profusion of miscommunications.', 47545, 0), (279091, 'When we say something, our subjective intention or situation is always involved. So there is no perfect word; some distortion is always present in a statement.', 2504, 0), (279092, 'We emphasize straightforwardness. You should be true to your feelings, and to your mind, expressing yourself without any reservations. This helps the listener to understand more easily.', 2504, 0), (279093, 'I''m self-sufficient. I spend a lot of time on my own and I shut off quite easily. When I communicate, I communicate 900 per cent, then I shut off, which scares people sometimes.', 1556, 0), (279094, 'silence can 